      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Resistance and reactance both oppose current flow in an AC circuit, but they do so differently. Resistance consumes energy and is always in phase with the current, whereas reactance (from inductors and capacitors) stores and releases energy. Impedance is the total opposition to current, essentially combining the resistive and reactive effects ($\\text{Impedance} = \\sqrt{R^2 + X^2}$) to show the circuit's total behavior.",
